## Experimentation Standards

Every experiment I run must answer:

1. What friction are we removing?
2. Does this increase activation or consistency?
3. Does this strengthen the behavior we are trying to build?
4. If it works, can it compound?
5. If it fails, what did we actually learn?

No hypothesis specifying friction and failure condition = not ready to launch.

The `/grill-me` skill operationalizes this standard. Aria fires it automatically as a pre-routing step on any net-new bet (experiment, journey, automation, agent pipeline, strategic decision) where the brief does not already specify friction-being-removed and failure condition. It caps at 10 questions and produces a structured brief. Routine execution (copy generation, polishing, recurring tasks) never triggers the grill.

